line_1: And by a splendid lustre doth outshine
line_2: By any other hand: She's all divine,

line_1: Which all your neighbours shall out-shine,
line_2: And of your Mind remain the Sign.

line_1: You said she did Noons Light out-shine,
line_2: More than the Paphian Queen Divine.

line_1: And neighb'ring Vermin with false Gloss outshine
line_2: Be here, my Son, content to Dress and Dine,

line_1: And neighb'ring Vermin with false Gloss outshine
line_2: Steeping the List of Beauties in thy Wine,

line_1: May all the beauties of the day outshine.
line_2: Enchanting creature! Charms so great as thine
